On EC2:
  create EC2 instance, create VPC and subnet, enable incound rules (port22 and port8080)
  save key.pem
  
On instance:
  1. Set up docker first
  - make the yml file
docker compose up -d

On local machine:
  1. Build jar
  2. Upload the jar to instance 
scp -i ~/Downloads/springbok-key.pem /Users/yuujadz/Downloads/Rothur_code-Nov-3-class-code/target/demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar ubuntu@<EC2-IP>:/home/ubuntu/

Once uploaded, ssh into the instance
ssh -i ~/Downloads/springbok-key.pem ubuntu@<EC2-IP>

(run docker)
check docker: docker ps
run docker: docker compose up -d

Start app
nohup java -jar demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar --server.port=8080 > app.log 2>&1 &

Validate started
ps aux | grep demo

Kill app
pkill -f demo-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar || true


